The Trump Administration aims to achieve economic growth through a new tax plan, which includes reform, regulatory relief, higher trade incentives, and a simplified tax code. Secretary Mnunchin hosted a listening session with agricultural industry leaders to discuss tax reform. Business leaders expressed concerns about fluctuating income, interest deductibility, and cost recovery provisions. The agriculture industry executives agreed that increased structure within the tax system would be beneficial for maintaining affordable food sources. Secretary Mnunchin emphasized the importance of listening to the public to ensure a favorable tax plan is passed.